solutionCode.javascript:
    ```javascript
function getXORSum(arr1, arr2) {
    let xor_arr1 = 0, xor_arr2 = 0;
    for (let i of arr1) xor_arr1 ^= i;
    for (let j of arr2) xor_arr2 ^= j;
    return xor_arr1 & xor_arr2;
}
```

    1. Initialize two variables `xor_arr1` and `xor_arr2` to store the XOR sum of arr1 and arr2, respectively.
2. Iterate over `arr1` and compute its XOR sum by using the XOR `^=` operator.
3. Iterate over `arr2` and compute its XOR sum similarly.
4. Return the bitwise AND `&` of the two computed XOR sums (`xor_arr1` and `xor_arr2`). As per the problem statement, this will be the XOR sum of the list containing the result of arr1[i] AND arr2[j].

